# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env
#    cp .env.example .env

# 2. Fill in your Supabase credentials
#    - Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
#    - Select your project
#    - Go to Settings > API
#    - Copy the URL and anon/public key

# 3. Set up Stripe
#    - Sign up at https://stripe.com
#    - Get your test API keys from the dashboard
#    - Add VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY to .env
#    - Set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY in Supabase secrets (see below)

# 4. Set up Clerk (Authentication)
#    - Sign up at https://clerk.com
#    - Create a new application
#    - Go to API Keys and copy the Publishable Key
#    - Add VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY to .env
#    - Set CLERK_SECRET_KEY and CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET in Supabase secrets

# 5. Set up Resend (Email Service)
#    - Sign up at https://resend.com
#    - Create an API key
#    - Set RESEND_API_KEY in Supabase secrets (see below)

# 6. Configure Supabase Edge Function Secrets
#    supabase login
#    supabase link --project-ref your-project-id
#    supabase secrets set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
#    supabase secrets set RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
#    supabase secrets set CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
#    supabase secrets set CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
#    supabase secrets set VITE_APP_URL=http://localhost:8080

# 7. Deploy Edge Functions
#    supabase functions deploy create-payment-intent
#    supabase functions deploy send-email
#    supabase functions deploy check-permissions
#    supabase functions deploy clerk-webhook

# 8. Apply Database Migrations
#    supabase db push

# 9. Configure Clerk Webhooks
#    - Go to Clerk Dashboard > Webhooks
#    - Add endpoint: https://your-project.supabase.co/functions/v1/clerk-webhook
#    - Subscribe to events: user.created, user.updated, user.deleted
#    - Copy the webhook secret and set it in Supabase secrets

# 10. Create Storage Buckets
#    - Go to Supabase Dashboard > Storage
#    - Create public buckets: 'avatars', 'products'
#    - Create private bucket: 'documents'
#    - Or use CLI:
#      supabase storage create avatars --public
#      supabase storage create products --public
#      supabase storage create documents

